title: RunTest

This fixture documents what `code-body: yes` ACTUALLY does in TW 5.4.0,
which contradicts an older memory claim.

normal-transclude: [<$transclude $tiddler="NormalTiddler"/>]
code-body-transclude: [<$transclude $tiddler="CodeBodyTiddler"/>]

If memory's claim ("code-body disables pragma parsing") were true,
code-body-transclude would render literal `\procedure greet() HELLO  <<greet>>`.
It does not — it renders HELLO. `code-body` only affects which
ViewTemplateBody is selected in the BROWSER view (cascade redirects
to $:/core/ui/ViewTemplate/body/code which shows raw text). It does
NOT change the wikitext parser. So pragmas still register and
transclusion / --render still evaluate them.
